    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Study of the Effect of Multiple Passage HTF Tubes on the Solar Thermal Energy Storage for Air Dryer</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Praharsha Sunkara, Venkatesh R</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Effect of Multiple Passage<br />Solar Thermal Energy Storage</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5405</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Renewable energy is the energy which comes from natural resources such as sunlight, wind, rain, tides, and geothermal heat, which are renewable (naturally replenished). About 16% of global final energy consumption comes from renewable. Todayâ€™s world is trying to use the best possible energy for day to day life. The solar energy is one kind of renewable sources of energy that is used or encouraged to be used in every country. Solar energy, radiant light and heat from the sun, has been harnessed by humans since ancient times using a range of ever-evolving technologies. In the present day, the way we use the energy is not important but how effectively are we using this energy and how well are we able to store and retrieve it is important.
The main aim of our project is to increase the Thermal Energy Storage efficiency by the usage of Phase Change Material as an energy storage medium and a Solar Double Reflector as an Energy Source. This project involved an experimental investigation for the performance enhancement of solar thermal energy storage system using different tube configurations inside the PCM. Three different types of tube configurations have been used to increase the rate of heat transfer between HTF and phase change material. A tubular heat exchanger is designed and tested for its thermal performance.
This report summarizes the investigation and analysis of solar thermal energy storage system. The thermal energy is extracted from solar collector is used for domestic and industrial purposes.SAE 40 Oil and a phase change material ( MgCl2.6H2O ) have been used one at a time for hot thermal energy storage. In this analysis, PCM and the oil are kept in the container. The PCM is used to preheat the atmospheric air supply and the hot air is used for variety of drying, heating applications in food, agricultural, process industries. PCM is stored in Stainless Steel vessel which is welded on copper disc with fin and a tube for the passage of the HTF.
Different tube configurations have been designed to test their effectiveness and to enhance the energy storage capacity of the Thermal Energy Storage system in which the PCM plays a vital role for the complete transfers of energy. A test setup is fabricated and experiments are conducted to study these aspects under laboratory conditions.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8576">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8576</a></td></tr>
